---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Contact">
    <section class="section">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p class="lead">
        Open to interesting projects involving operational workflows, data systems, 
        and process automation.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="contact-info">
        <div class="contact-item">
        <h3>Email</h3>
        <p>
            <a href="mailto:your@email.com">your@email.com</a>
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted">
            Best for project inquiries, collaboration opportunities, or questions 
            about my work.
        </p>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-item">
        <h3>Location</h3>
        <p>Tokyo, Japan</p>
        <p class="text-muted">
            Available for remote work across time zones. Open to travel for the 
            right projects.
        </p>
        </div>

        <div class="contact-item">
        <h3>Response time</h3>
        <p>Usually within 24-48 hours</p>
        <p class="text-muted">
            I read every email. If you don't hear back, check your spam folder 
            or try reaching out again.
        </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
        <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
        <p>Projects where I can help:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>Automating manual operational processes</li>
        <li>Building or fixing data pipelines</li>
        <li>Integrating systems that don't talk to each other</li>
        <li>Creating dashboards and reporting tools</li>
        <li>Optimizing workflows and removing bottlenecks</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section-last">
        <h2>Not a good fit</h2>
        <p>I'm probably not the right person for:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>Frontend-heavy projects (not my strength)</li>
        <li>Mobile app development</li>
        <li>Pure design work</li>
        <li>Projects requiring deep ML/AI expertise</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
        If you're unsure whether your project fits, reach out anyway. 
        I'll let you know honestly if I can help or point you toward someone who can.
        </p>
    </section>
    </QuietGridLayout>

    <style>
    .section {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
        padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
    
    .section-last {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }
    
    .lead {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    
    .contact-info {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: var(--space-xl);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }
    
    .contact-item {
        padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
    
    .contact-item:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
    }
    
    .contact-item h3 {
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    }
    
    .contact-item p {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    }
    
    .contact-item p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    
    ul {
        list-style: none;
        margin: var(--space-md) 0;
    }
    
    ul li {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
        position: relative;
    }
    
    ul li::before {
        content: 'â€”';
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }
</style>